# Bandit OverTheWire – Levels 1–10

## Objective
Develop foundational Linux and security skills through hands-on challenges involving file access, permissions, and basic command-line usage.

## Tools Used
- Linux terminal
- SSH

## What I Did
- Connected to Bandit servers using SSH
- Navigated directories using basic Linux commands
- Located hidden files and read file contents
- Worked with file permissions and special characters in filenames
- Used commands like ls, cd, cat, file, and find

## Key Learnings
- Importance of file permissions in security
- How hidden files can contain sensitive data
- Basic Linux navigation and enumeration techniques
- Handling unusual filenames and directory structures

## Skills Gained
- Linux command-line proficiency
- File system navigation
- Basic enumeration techniques
- Problem-solving in a security context

## Notes
This lab helped build a strong foundation for understanding how attackers and defenders interact with Linux systems.
